.TH test-printer 1 "2026-01-02" "foo2zjs"
.SH NAME
test-printer.sh \- test installed printer configuration for foo2zjs driver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B test-printer.sh
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ printer-name ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B test-printer.sh
is a utility script to test and verify that printers using the foo2zjs
driver suite are properly installed and configured. It can check printer
status, list available printers, verify dependencies, and send test pages.
.PP
This script is particularly useful after installing or configuring a new
printer to ensure that all components are working correctly.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display usage information and exit.
.TP
.B \-l, \-\-list
List all installed printers on the system.
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-status
Check the status of the specified printer (or default printer if none specified).
Shows printer state, current jobs, and driver information.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-test-page
Send a test page to the specified printer (or default printer if none specified).
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-check-deps
Check if all required dependencies are installed. This includes:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
CUPS (lpstat, lpr)
.IP \(bu 2
Ghostscript (gs)
.IP \(bu 2
Optional: usb_printerid
.RE
.TP
.B \-a, \-\-all
Run all tests: check dependencies, list printers, and check printer status.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output for debugging.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I printer-name
The name of the printer to test. If not specified, the system default
printer will be used. Use the
.B \-l
option to see available printer names.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Check if all dependencies are installed:
.nf
test-printer.sh -c
.fi
.TP
List all available printers:
.nf
test-printer.sh -l
.fi
.TP
Check status of a specific printer:
.nf
test-printer.sh -s HP_LaserJet_1020
.fi
.TP
Send a test page to the default printer:
.nf
test-printer.sh -t
.fi
.TP
Run all tests on a specific printer:
.nf
test-printer.sh -a HP_LaserJet_1020
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred (printer not found, dependency missing, etc.)
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ./testpage.ps
Test page PostScript file in current directory
.TP
.I /usr/share/foo2zjs/testpage.ps
Installed test page PostScript file
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR foo2zjs (1),
.BR foo2zjs-wrapper (1),
.BR lpstat (1),
.BR lpr (1),
.BR gs (1)
